 The acting trio will be joined by an ensemble cast of Tinah Mnumzana, Don Mosenye, Noxee Maqashalala, Thabo Malema, Paballo Khoza, Sive Mabuya and Austin Shandu.The show is set to premiere on etv on Tuesday, 12 September, at 9:30pm.The plot follows the story of a 34-year-old history teacher Khosi (Zondi), who gets involved in a pyramid scheme.Chiume will portray Khosi s work colleague Gloria a maths teacher who invests her retirement money in the scheme.Phele plays Amos, described as the community construction worker.